---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import BreadcrumbSchema from "../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro";
const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: "Home", url: "https://walkscape-index.github.io" },
  { name: "Privacy Policy" },
];
---

<Layout
  site="WalkScape Index"
  title="Privacy Policy"
  tagline="How we handle your data and respect your privacy"
  pageTitle="Privacy Policy"
  pageDescription="Privacy Policy for WalkScape Index - The community resource directory for Walkscape tools, databases, and spreadsheets."
  showLatestFilter={false}
>
  <BreadcrumbSchema items={breadcrumbs} />

  <main id="main-content" class="container">
    <div class="legal-content-wrapper">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: May 17, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <article class="nu-u-text--secondary">
        <p class="nu-c-fs-regular">
          At WalkScape Index, accessible from https://walkscape-index.github.io,
          one of our main priorities is the privacy of our visitors. This
          Privacy Policy document contains types of information that is
          collected and recorded by WalkScape Index and how we use it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="nu-c-h6 nu-u-text--primary">1. Data Collection</h2>
        <p>
          WalkScape Index is a static website designed to provide a curated
          directory of Walkscape tools, databases, calculators, and
          spreadsheets. We do not require user registration and do not collect
          any personally identifiable information (PII) directly from you unless
          you choose to contact us through external open-source channels (e.g.,
          GitHub).
        </p>

        <h2 class="nu-c-h6 nu-u-text--primary">
          2. Local Storage (Saved Resources)
        </h2>
        <p>
          Our "Saved Tools" feature uses your browser's <strong
            class="nu-u-text--primary">localStorage</strong
          >
          to store the unique IDs of the resources you have bookmarked. This data
          is stored locally on your physical device and is never transmitted to an
          external server. You can wipe this data at any time by clearing your browser's
          cache or using the untag/remove options in the UI grid.
        </p>

        <h2 class="nu-c-h6 nu-u-text--primary">3. Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors interact with our
          index. Google Analytics uses cookies to track anonymized usage
          telemetry (e.g., page views, session duration, filter usage). This
          helps us optimize the layout grid for active users. You can opt-out by
          installing the official Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on.
        </p>

        <h2 class="nu-c-h6 nu-u-text--primary">4. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Like most modern web directories, we use essential cookies to optimize
          your experience. These are small text files stored on your device that
          help us remember your configuration states (such as dark theme toggles
          or active category filter selections).
        </p>

        <h2 class="nu-c-h6 nu-u-text--primary">5. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          Our directory indexes and links directly to external Walkscape
          utilities, hosted spreadsheets, and community platforms. We do not
          control and are not responsible for the data privacy frameworks or
          accurate content states of these external entities. We encourage you
          to check their individual source code or terms separately.
        </p>

        <h2 class="nu-c-h6 nu-u-text--primary">6. Consent</h2>
        <p>
          By using our index directory, you hereby consent to our Privacy Policy
          and agree to its terms.
        </p>

        <h2 class="nu-c-h6 nu-u-text--primary">7. Contact & Contributions</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions regarding this privacy notice, or want to
          report/update an outdated community link tag, feel free to open an
          issue or reach out via the official
          <a
            href="https://github.com/walkscape-index"
            class="nu-u-text--primary">walkscape-index</a
          >
          GitHub repository organization page.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
